        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 7:29AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 728 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
extending from near Bowie, to 6 miles south of Lake Amon G Carter,
to near Bryson. Movement was northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
St. Jo, Lost Creek Reservoir, Cundiff, Lake Nocona, Park Springs,
Capps Corner, Crafton, Nocona Hills, Bowie, Wizard Wells, Jermyn,
Jacksboro, Nocona, Fruitland, Fort Richardson State Park, Montague,
Ringgold, Forestburg, Illinois Bend, and Sunset.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
